# retry-after-not-honored.tflw — DEMO-FAIL FIXTURE (M24, testFlow PLAN.md decision 102b): a
# fresh `retry-demo` key with no `retry honoring "Retry-After" up to N` clause — the request is
# sent exactly once, sees the 429, and the test fails. Shows the gap `retry honoring` closes
# (TFLW-GAPS.md gap #5): without it, a genuinely rate-limited request just fails.
#
# Run explicitly (dot-directory, invisible to a bare `tflw run`/`tflw check`):
#   npx tflw run tests/.demo-fail/retry-after-not-honored.tflw --tag demofail

@demofail @retryafter
test "without the retry clause, a rate-limited request just fails"
  api POST /retry-demo body { key: random string 8 }
  expect status equals 200
